{"id":13546,"date":"2020-07-31T01:33:12","date_gmt":"2020-07-30T20:03:12","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/?p=13546"},"modified":"2022-01-25T01:57:02","modified_gmt":"2022-01-24T20:27:02","slug":"install-java-on-64-bit-windows","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/java\/basics\/install-java-on-64-bit-windows\/","title":{"rendered":"Installing Java on 64 bit Windows"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Learn to install Java on 64 bit Windows machines in this step-by-step guide.<\/p>\n<h2>1. Navigate to the Oracle Java Download Page<\/h2>\n<p>Navigate to the Java <a href=\"https:\/\/www.oracle.com\/java\/technologies\/javase-downloads.html\">download page<\/a> for the latest Java release. <\/p>\n<p>Click on the link <em>&#8220;JDK Download&#8221;<\/em>.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_13559\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13559\" style=\"width: 835px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Download-Link.jpg\" alt=\"JDK Download Link\" width=\"845\" height=\"371\" class=\"size-full wp-image-13559\" srcset=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Download-Link.jpg 845w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Download-Link-300x132.jpg 300w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Download-Link-768x337.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 845px) 100vw, 845px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-13559\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">JDK Download Link<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h2>2. Download the zip or exe Package<\/h2>\n<p>Here you have two choices:<\/p>\n<h4>2.1. Windows x64 Installer<\/h4>\n<p>An <code>.exe<\/code> file which installs the Java in your 64-bit windows machine and makes all necessary environment entries. <\/p>\n<blockquote><p>For a normal user, it is the best approach.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<h4>2.2. Windows x64 Compressed Archive<\/h4>\n<p>A <code>.zip<\/code> file distribution which you can copy to any location the computer. In this case, you need to update all the required environment variables (e.g. PATH, JAVA_HOME, etc.) yourself.<\/p>\n<p>It is best suited for Java developers who want to keep multiple versions of Java running on their computers. <\/p>\n<p>After clicking any of the download links, a popup will appear to accept <em>Oracle Technology Network License Agreement for Oracle Java SE<\/em> in order to download this software. Click on the checkbox and then proceed to download it.<\/p>\n<p>Login to the oracle website if prompted.<\/p>\n<h2>3. Installation with <code>.exe<\/code> File<\/h2>\n<p>If we are installing the Java software with the <code>exe<\/code> file downloaded in the previous section, follow the given steps. <\/p>\n<h4>Step 1. Double click on exe file to initiate the installation process<\/h4>\n<figure id=\"attachment_13551\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13551\" style=\"width: 492px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Step-1.jpg\" alt=\"Step-1\" width=\"502\" height=\"380\" class=\"size-full wp-image-13551\" srcset=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Step-1.jpg 502w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Step-1-300x227.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 502px) 100vw, 502px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-13551\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Step-1<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h4>Step 2. Select Java installation location<\/h4>\n<p>Until you have a reason to change the location, let it be the default location. <\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_13552\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13552\" style=\"width: 488px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Step-2.jpg\" alt=\"Step-2\" width=\"498\" height=\"380\" class=\"size-full wp-image-13552\" srcset=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Step-2.jpg 498w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Step-2-300x229.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 498px) 100vw, 498px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-13552\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Step-2<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h4>Step 3. Begin Java Installation<\/h4>\n<p>Click on <code>Next<\/code> button and it will install Java in your 64-bit computer. After the process complete in a few minutes, the installation wizard will end with a success message.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_13553\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13553\" style=\"width: 486px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Installation-Finished.jpg\" alt=\"JDK Installation Finished\" width=\"496\" height=\"376\" class=\"size-full wp-image-13553\" srcset=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Installation-Finished.jpg 496w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Installation-Finished-300x227.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 496px) 100vw, 496px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-13553\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">JDK Installation Finished<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h2>4. Installation with <code>.zip<\/code> File<\/h2>\n<p>This process is more suited for the Java developers community. Using this process, you can have multiple versions of Java on your computer. So based on the project requirements, you can choose a different version of any of the projects.<\/p>\n<h4>Step 1. Extract the zip archive in desired location<\/h4>\n<p>I have unzipped the <code>jdk-14.0.2_windows-x64_bin.zip<\/code> file in this location: <code>E:\\devsetup\\jdk-14<\/code>.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_13554\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13554\" style=\"width: 648px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Unzip-the-file-in-desired-location.jpg\" alt=\"Unzip the file in desired location\" width=\"658\" height=\"273\" class=\"size-full wp-image-13554\" srcset=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Unzip-the-file-in-desired-location.jpg 658w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Unzip-the-file-in-desired-location-300x124.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-13554\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Unzip the file in desired location<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h4>Step 2. Add\/Update the environment properties<\/h4>\n<p>To find the environment properties window, look for it in the control panel. Or in Windows 10, directly search it in the search box in the taskbar.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_13557\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13557\" style=\"width: 374px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Find-environment-variables.png\" alt=\"Find environment variables\" width=\"384\" height=\"494\" class=\"size-full wp-image-13557\" srcset=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Find-environment-variables.png 384w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Find-environment-variables-233x300.png 233w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-13557\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Find environment variables<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Add the <strong>JAVA_HOME<\/strong> variable and specify the folder path as value, where you unzipped the downloaded Java package.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_13555\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13555\" style=\"width: 670px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Add-JAVA_HOME.jpg\" alt=\"Add JAVA_HOME\" width=\"680\" height=\"200\" class=\"size-full wp-image-13555\" srcset=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Add-JAVA_HOME.jpg 680w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Add-JAVA_HOME-300x88.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-13555\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Add JAVA_HOME<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Now update the <code>PATH<\/code> variable. Add a new path in the list which is the <code>bin<\/code> folder inside the JDK folder.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_13558\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13558\" style=\"width: 600px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/The-PATH-Variable-to-Edit.jpg\" alt=\"The PATH Variable to Edit\" width=\"610\" height=\"301\" class=\"size-full wp-image-13558\" srcset=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/The-PATH-Variable-to-Edit.jpg 610w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/The-PATH-Variable-to-Edit-300x148.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-13558\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The PATH Variable to Edit<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<figure id=\"attachment_13556\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13556\" style=\"width: 519px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Update-PATH-variable.jpg\" alt=\"Update PATH variable\" width=\"529\" height=\"499\" class=\"size-full wp-image-13556\" srcset=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Update-PATH-variable.jpg 529w, https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Update-PATH-variable-300x283.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 529px) 100vw, 529px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-13556\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Update PATH variable<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>After both variables are updated, we can validate the Java installation.<\/p>\n<h2>5. Verify Java Installation<\/h2>\n<p>To verify that Java has been installed on your computer, open a new command prompt. Type the below command which will print the version of Java installed on your computer.<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: java; title: Java Version Command; notranslate\" title=\"Java Version Command\">\r\n&gt; java -version\r\n<\/pre>\n<p>The command output.<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: java; title: Console; notranslate\" title=\"Console\">\r\njava version &quot;14&quot; 2020-03-17\r\nJava(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 14+36-1461)\r\nJava HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 14+36-1461, mixed mode, sharing)\r\n<\/pre>\n<p>image<\/p>\n<p>If you get any error in running this command, verify all the steps listed above. <\/p>\n<p>Happy Learning !!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Learn to install Java on 64 bit Windows machines in this step-by-step guide. 1. Navigate to the Oracle Java Download Page Navigate to the Java download page for the latest Java release. Click on the link &#8220;JDK Download&#8221;. 2. Download the zip or exe Package Here you have two choices: 2.1. Windows x64 Installer An &#8230; <a title=\"Installing Java on 64 bit Windows\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/java\/basics\/install-java-on-64-bit-windows\/\" aria-label=\"More on Installing Java on 64 bit Windows\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":13559,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[753],"tags":[602,538],"uagb_featured_image_src":{"full":["https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Download-Link.jpg",845,371,false],"thumbnail":["https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Download-Link-150x150.jpg",150,150,true],"medium":["https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Download-Link-300x132.jpg",300,132,true],"medium_large":["https:\/\/howtodoinjava.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/JDK-Download-Link-768x337.jpg",768,337,tr